# Reduce EAS archive size (critical for monorepo + pnpm + large vendored native bits).
# EAS respects this + .gitignore when creating the upload tarball from the project directory.

# === Heavy iOS-only / Android-irrelevant (big win for Android builds) ===
modules/t3-terminal/Vendor/**
**/*.xcframework/**
**/*-arm64*.a
**/*-simulator/**

# === Generated native projects (never commit these) ===
android/**
ios/**

# === Local / dev / build artifacts ===
.expo/**
.expo-shared/**
dist/**
web-build/**
*.log
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store

# === Things the EAS worker can re-install / doesn't need in the archive ===
# (pnpm monorepo means real deps live in root via symlinks; these patterns help the packer)
node_modules/**
.pnpm/**
**/node_modules/**
**/.pnpm/**

# === Docs, tests, examples inside deps (safe to drop) ===
node_modules/**/docs/**
node_modules/**/example/**
node_modules/**/test/**
node_modules/**/__tests__/**
node_modules/**/coverage/**

# Keep the *source* of our custom expo modules (file: deps) and the small nitro tgz.
# The heavy compiled artifacts inside them are already covered above.

# Additional aggressive excludes for size (shiki languages, etc. are pulled in via workspace)
**/@shikijs/**
**/shiki/**
**/@shikijs/langs/**
**/@shikijs/themes/**

# Note: because this is a pnpm workspace, a lot of the real dependency content
# lives in the repo-root node_modules/.pnpm via symlinks. The packer may still
# pull a large amount of JS. .easignore + running from apps/mobile (or GitHub base dir)
# is the best we can do. The archive will still be large (~100MB+). 

# For even smaller uploads in CI, consider using EAS's "builds" config or a separate
# lightweight checkout, but the current setup works for local/CI as documented.
